info.senderName: NWS Cheyenne (Southeastern Wyoming and Western Nebraska)
info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 14 at 2:16PM CST until February 14 at 7:00PM CST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM MST THIS EVENING... * WHAT...West to northwest winds 35 to 45 MPH with gusts up to 65 MPH. * WHERE...In Wyoming, Platte and Laramie Counties including the cities of Wheatland, Chugwater, Cheyenne, and Pine Bluffs. In Nebraska, Kimball and Cheyenne counties including the cities of Kimball and Sidney. * WHEN...Until 6 PM MST this evening. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
